    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"></p>
<h3>Exercise 4: Reverse the Digits</h3>
<p>Write a C program that prompts the user to enter a two-digit positive integer, then prints the number with its digits reversed.  E.g.</p>
<p></p>
<pre>Enter a two-digit positive integer: 35 <br>The reversal is: 53</pre>
<p>This can be achieved using either a char array and swapping the values, or it can be done by reading the user input as an integer using "%d" and then using arithmetic (modulo and divide) to get the desired result. if the input is not exactly a two-digit positive integer, your program should print "<span class="" style="font-family: 'Courier New', Courier, mono;">Invalid input!</span>" and a newline, and exit.</p>
<p>Save your work as <strong>exercise04.c</strong> and ensure that it compiles and runs without error:</p>
<pre>gcc exercise04.c -pedantic -Wall -o exercise04<br>./exercise04</pre>
<p></p>
<p></p>]]></text>
